<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="579" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,259,1402]" pageId="12" pageNumber="579">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,835,861]" pageId="12" pageNumber="579">Description.</emphasis>
Male (
<typeStatus box="[432,537,835,862]" pageId="12" pageNumber="579">holotype</typeStatus>
). Total length 10.3. Carapace: 5.1 long, 4.25 wide. General appearance as in 
<figureCitation box="[151,223,871,897]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–9" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1832,1856]" captionTargetBox="[157,1436,189,1799]" captionTargetId="figure-33@2.[151,1436,181,1809]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–9. General appearance of Acantholycosa sayanensis (1–2), A. kulikovi sp. n. (3), A. levinae (4–5), A. sergeevi sp. n. (6), Mongolicosa lizae sp. n. (8–9) and leg I of A. sergeevi sp. n. (7). 1, 4, 6, 8—male, dorsal; 2, 3, 5, 9—female, dorsal; 7—leg I of male, prolateral. Scale bars=2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5300794" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5300794/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="579">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
. Coloration. Carapace and chelicerae black. Sternum and labium dark-brown. Endites yellow-gray. Palps black. Coxae yellow-gray with yellow spots. Legs dark brown, almost black. Legs I–III have a thick cotton-like pubescence of curled hairs. Abdomen dark gray dorsally, almost black. Cardiac mark dark brown. Venter of the abdomen yellow-gray. Spinnerets black. Spination of leg I: Fe d1-1-1 p0-0-3 r0-1-1; Pa p1 r1; Ti d1-0-1 p1-0-0 v2- 2-2-2-2-2-2-2; Mt p1-1-0 r1-1-0 v2-2-0. Leg measurements: I 4.6, 2.2, 4.35, 4.15, 1.85 (17.15); II 4.55, 2.15, 4.2, 4.25, 1.95 (17.1); III 4.6, 2.0, 3.85, 5.45, 2.05 (17.95); IV 5.35, 2.05, 4.8, 7.85, 2.55 (22.6).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,259,1402]" pageId="12" pageNumber="579">
Palp as in 
<figureCitation box="[317,445,1087,1113]" captionStart="FIGURES 10–19" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1849,1873]" captionTargetBox="[155,1425,188,1810]" captionTargetId="figure-15@3.[151,1436,181,1825]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 10–19. Male palp (10–13) and bulb (14–19) of Acantholycosa sergeevi sp. n. (10–11), A. sayanensis (14–15), A. sidorovi sp. n. (16–17), A. levinae (18-19) and Mongolicosa lizae sp. n. (12–13). 10, 12—retrolateral; 11, 13, 14, 16, 18— ventral; 15, 17, 19—anterior. Scale bars=0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5300796" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5300796/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="579">Figs 10–11</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[457,530,1087,1113]" captionStart="FIGURES 32–43" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1742,1766]" captionTargetBox="[154,1435,189,1719]" captionTargetId="figure-33@6.[151,1437,181,1719]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 32–43. Tegulum and subtegulum (32–37), bulb (38–40) and embolic division (41–43) of Acantholycosa sayanensis (32–33), A. sidorovi sp. n. (34–35), A. levinae (36–37) and A. sergeevi sp. n. (38–43). 32, 34, 36, 38, 41—ventral; 33, 35, 37, 39, 42—anterior; 40, 43—retrolateral. Scale bars=0.2 mm. Abbreviations: Aa apical arm of the tegular apophysis, Ba basal arm of the tegular apophysis, Em embolus, Pe extension of the palea, Pl palea, Ta terminal apophysis, Tg tegular apophysis, Ts triangle-shaped projection of the palea." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5300798" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5300798/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="579">38–43</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[542,616,1087,1114]" captionStart="FIGURES 44–53" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1794,1818]" captionTargetBox="[163,1427,188,1770]" captionTargetId="figure-15@7.[151,1436,181,1770]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 44–53. Tegulum and subtegulum (44–45, 52–53), bulb (46–48) and embolic division (49–51) of Acantholycosa sergeevi sp. n. (44–45) and Mongolicosa lizae sp. n. (46–53). 44, 46, 49, 52—ventral; 45, 47, 50, 53—anterior; 48, 51— retrolateral. Scale bars=0.2 mm. Abbreviations: Aa apical arm of the tegular apophysis, Ba basal arm of the tegular apophysis, Em embolus, Pl palea, Sd sperm duct, Ta terminal apophysis, Tg tegular apophysis." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5300800" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5300800/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="579">44–45</figureCitation>
. Tegular apophysis hammer-shaped, with reduced apical arm. Palea with abrupt retrolateral margin. Triangle-shaped projection straight and sharply pointed, bearing conical tubercle on the retrolateral edge. Terminal apophysis massive, subdivided into two lobes. Embolus completely straight. Distal part of the embolus bears a rectangular laminar outgrowth on the anterior edge.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,259,1402]" box="[199,401,1231,1257]" pageId="12" pageNumber="579">Female unknown.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,1276,1267,1294]" pageId="12" pageNumber="579" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,259,1402]" box="[199,1276,1267,1294]" pageId="12" pageNumber="579">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,353,1267,1293]" pageId="12" pageNumber="579">Distribution.</emphasis>
Known only from the 
<typeStatus box="[608,656,1268,1294]" pageId="12" pageNumber="579">type</typeStatus>
locality in the Western Sayan Mountains (
<figureCitation box="[1132,1264,1267,1294]" captionStart="FIGURES 72–77" captionStartId="13.[151,264,1676,1700]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,309,1652]" captionTargetId="figure-76@13.[151,1436,309,1652]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 72–77. Male of Acantholycosa sayanensis from Borus Mt. Range (72), female of Acantholycosa sp. (A. azyuzini or A. levinae) with egg sac, from Katunskyi Mt. Range (73), habitat of A. sayanensis and A. sergeevi sp. n. in Borus Mt. Range (74), collecting localities of studied species from the Acantholycosa-complex (75–76) and map showing the main mountain systems of South Siberia and adjacent regions (77). Diamond—A. sayanensis, square—A. sidorovi sp. n., triangle—A. kulikovi sp. n., star—A. levinae, circle—A. sergeevi sp. n., inverted triangle—Mongolicosa lizae sp. n. The frame of Fig. 76 refers to the content of Fig. 75." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5300806" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5300806/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="579">Figs 74–76</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="579" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,259,1402]" pageId="12" pageNumber="579">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,335,1303,1329]" pageId="12" pageNumber="579">Comments.</emphasis>
This species was found in the same locality and in the same scree patches as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Marusik, Azarkina &amp; Koponen" authorityYear="2004" class="Arachnida" family="Lycosidae" genus="Acantholycosa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="12" pageNumber="579" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sayanensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="579">Acantholycosa sayanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see above). Interestingly, 
<taxonomicName authority="Fomichev, 2021" authorityName="Fomichev" authorityYear="2021" box="[581,706,1339,1365]" class="Arachnida" family="Lycosidae" genus="Acantholycosa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="12" pageNumber="579" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sergeevi" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[581,706,1339,1365]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="579">A. sergeevi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[714,779,1339,1365]" pageId="12" pageNumber="579">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[714,779,1339,1365]" pageId="12" pageNumber="579" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
is much rarer than 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Marusik, Azarkina &amp; Koponen" authorityYear="2004" box="[1003,1156,1339,1365]" class="Arachnida" family="Lycosidae" genus="Acantholycosa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="12" pageNumber="579" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sayanensis">
<emphasis box="[1003,1156,1339,1365]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="579">A. sayanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The 
<typeStatus box="[1223,1321,1339,1365]" pageId="12" pageNumber="579">holotype</typeStatus>
male was collected together with 
<specimenCount box="[415,567,1375,1401]" pageId="12" pageNumber="579" type="generic">30 specimens</specimenCount>
of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Marusik, Azarkina &amp; Koponen" authorityYear="2004" box="[604,756,1375,1401]" class="Arachnida" family="Lycosidae" genus="Acantholycosa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="12" pageNumber="579" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sayanensis">
<emphasis box="[604,756,1375,1401]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="579">A. sayanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
